// `extend service UserService` — splits the admin operations of
// UserService into a separate file in the SAME PACKAGE. The
// analyser enforces:
//
//   - the primary `service UserService { ... }` must exist somewhere
//     in package `services` (orphan extends fire
//     `service/extend-orphan`).
//   - `extend service` blocks may NOT carry service-level decorators
//     — those live on the primary; per-method `@middlewares(...)`
//     and `@errors(...)` are still fair game (and APPEND to the
//     primary's chain).
//
// Here BanUser layers on a cross-package `shared.RateLimit`
// middleware so admin actions are throttled tighter than the
// primary CRUD surface.
package services

import "shared"

extend service UserService {
	@middlewares(shared.RateLimit)
	post BanUser /{id}/ban {
		request  UserRef
		response User
	}
}
